<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="59" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[807,1461,324,442]" box="[807,1280,417,442]" pageId="3" pageNumber="59">
Current accepted name: 
<taxonomicName authority="L." box="[1072,1280,417,441]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="3" pageNumber="59" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="capense">
<emphasis box="[1072,1250,417,441]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="59">Solanum capense</emphasis>
L.
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[807,1461,462,1074]" pageId="3" pageNumber="59">
No material filed as 
<taxonomicName box="[1051,1203,462,486]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="3" pageNumber="59" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="subbiflorum">
<emphasis box="[1051,1203,462,486]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="59">S. subbiflorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was found in the general herbarium, in the list of plants used by Cavanilles in teaching in the year 1801 (
<bibRefCitation author="Cavanilles, A. J." box="[1052,1236,524,548]" journalOrPublisher="Imprenta Real, Madrid" pageId="3" pageNumber="59" refId="ref4381" refString="Cavanilles, A. J. 1802. Descripcion de las plantas que D. Antonio Josef Cavanilles demostro en las lecciones publicas del ano 1801. Imprenta Real, Madrid." title="Descripcion de las plantas que D. Antonio Josef Cavanilles demostro en las lecciones publicas del ano 1801" type="book" year="1802">Cavanilles, 1802</bibRefCitation>
) 
<taxonomicName box="[1253,1410,524,548]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="3" pageNumber="59" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="subbiflorum">
<emphasis box="[1253,1410,524,548]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="59">S. subbiflorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was recognised as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="Jacq." authorityName="Jacq." box="[1109,1340,555,579]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="3" pageNumber="59" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="milleri">
<emphasis box="[1109,1278,555,579]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="59">Solanum milleri</emphasis>
Jacq.
</taxonomicName>
(itself a synonym of 
<taxonomicName box="[915,1020,586,609]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="3" pageNumber="59" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="capense">
<emphasis box="[915,1020,586,609]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="59">S. capense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L.).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[807,1461,462,1074]" pageId="3" pageNumber="59">
Filed as 
<taxonomicName box="[927,1096,616,640]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="3" pageNumber="59" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="milleri">
<emphasis box="[927,1096,616,640]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="59">Solanum milleri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the general herbarium are several sheets, two were not collected from plants cultivated “en el jardín de esta Corte”; MA 573873 is a specimen donated by a secondary school in San Isidro and MA 308506 was collected on an unknown date by a Sr. Pascal. Two additional sheets are from material cultivated at the Real Jardín Botánico; one is too late to have been collected from the same plant Gómez Ortega used for his description (MA 3084902, dated 1844). MA 308482 (
<figureCitation box="[960,1046,864,888]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[130,162,1926,1945]" captionTargetBox="[253,1353,185,1905]" captionTargetId="figure-78@2.[253,1353,185,1906]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 1. a, neotype of Solanum cymosum Ortega (=Solanum lanceolatum Cav.) (MA 476353); b, neotype of Solanum ficifolium Ortega (= Solanum ferrugineum Jacq.) (MA 334586); c, neotype of Solanum leprosum Ortega (=Solanum elaeagnifolium Cav.) (MA 334600); d, neotype of Solanum subbiflorum Ortega (=Solanum capense L.) (MA308482)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6327660" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6327660/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="59">Fig. 1d</figureCitation>
) is annotated as “ 
<taxonomicName authority="Jacq." authorityName="Jacq." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="3" pageNumber="59" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="milleri">Solanum milleri Jacq.</taxonomicName>
/ 
<taxonomicName authority="Ortega" authorityName="Ortega" box="[868,1188,895,919]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="3" pageNumber="59" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="subbiflorum">Solanum subbiflorum Ortega</taxonomicName>
/ Ex Hort. Matr. 1803” in the hand of José Demetrio Rodriguez and is likely to be material from the same plants used by Gómez Ortega three years earlier to describe 
<taxonomicName box="[1080,1236,988,1012]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="3" pageNumber="59" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="subbiflorum">
<emphasis box="[1080,1236,988,1012]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="59">S. subbiflorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and I have selected this sheet as the neotype. All of these sheets are identifiable as 
<taxonomicName box="[807,911,1050,1074]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="3" pageNumber="59" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="capense">
<emphasis box="[807,911,1050,1074]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="59">S. capense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
